A Magistrate Court in Port Harcourt has remanded one Victor Elem at the Nigerian Correctional Center in Port Harcourt on a charge bothering on defilement. In a charge sheet, the 60 years old man is accused of defiling a 12 years old physically challenged girl inside her parentâ€™s apartment in Ubima Community in Ikwerre Local Government Area of the state. When the matter was mentioned in court, the Chief Magistrate, Kobani-Buzugbe declined jurisdiction to hear the case and directed that the case file be sent to the Department of Public Prosecution for advice. Chief Magistrate Kobani-Buzugbe subsequently adjourned to 23rd May 2022 for legal advice.